    "topic": "Compound Interest - Half Yearly/Quarterly",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Half-Yearly Compounding",
        "content": "If interest is compounded half-yearly:\nRate becomes R/2 and Time becomes 2T\n\n**Example:**\nP = ₹2000, R = 10% p.a., T = 1 year (half-yearly)\nCI = 2000 × (1 + 5/100)^2 − 2000 = ₹2205 − ₹2000 = ₹205"
      },
      {
        "subtopic": "Quarterly Compounding",
        "content": "If interest is compounded quarterly:\nRate becomes R/4 and Time becomes 4T\n\n**Example:**\nP = ₹1600, R = 8% p.a., T = 1 year (quarterly)\nCI = 1600 × (1 + 2/100)^4 − 1600 = ₹1731.85 − ₹1600 = ₹131.85"
      }
    ]
  },
