    "topic": "Difference Between Simple and Compound Interest",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Key Comparison",
        "content": "Simple Interest is calculated only on the principal amount.\nCompound Interest is calculated on principal + interest.\n\n**Example:**\nP = ₹1000, R = 10%, T = 2 years\nSI = 1000 × 10 × 2 / 100 = ₹200\nCI = 1000 × (1.1)^2 − 1000 = ₹1210 − ₹1000 = ₹210\n**Difference = ₹10**"
